Integration Testing of DynamoDB

  Configure <<<jcabi-heroku-maven-plugin>>> in your <<<pom.xml>>>:

+--
<project>
  <build>
    <plugins>
      <plugin>
        <groupId>com.jcabi</groupId>
        <artifactId>jcabi-dynamodb-maven-plugin</artifactId>
        <version>${project.version}</version>
        <configuration>
          <port>12345</port>
        </configuration>
        <executions>
          <execution>
            <goals>
              <goal>start</goal>
              <goal>stop</goal>
            </goals>
          </execution>
        </executions>
      </plugin>
    </plugins>
  </build>
</project>
+--

  In your integration tests make sure that you set correct
  entry point for AWS Dynamo.

* Cutting Edge Version

  If you want to use current version of the product, you can do it with
  this configuration in your <<<pom.xml>>>:

+--
<pluginRepositories>
  <pluginRepository>
    <id>oss.sonatype.org</id>
    <url>https://oss.sonatype.org/content/repositories/snapshots/</url>
  </pluginRepository>
</pluginRepositories>
<build>
  <plugins>
    <plugin>
      <groupId>com.jcabi</groupId>
      <artifactId>jcabi-heroku-maven-plugin</artifactId>
      <version>1.0-SNAPSHOT</version>
      [...]
    </plugin>
  </plugins>
</build>
+--
